<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,535,559,585]" box="[189,535,559,585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,535,559,585]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,535,559,585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution and bionomics</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,605,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The representatives of the new subtribe are distributed in the deserts of Central and South Asia (
<collectingCountry box="[197,364,640,666]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[378,428,641,667]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[440,586,640,666]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[600,702,640,666]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[717,793,640,667]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">China</collectingCountry>
): Karakum, Dasht-e Lut, Dasht-e Kewir, Registan, Taklamakan. Species of the mentioned genera inhabit non-fixed barchan sand dunes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
